originalText.text: Our experience with Caroline was phenomenal from start to finish! Hanging our with her was wonderful, the photos turned out amazing and she did a fantastic job on the album and the photos we got framed. I usually look awkward in pictures, but she made us feel so relaxed on our wedding day that the only thing that shines through is how happy we were! I think the best part was that Caroline was so helpful in ways I wasn't expecting - such as helping us allocate enough time for photos and plan the timeline for the day. Caroline was definitely a big part of helping our day go so smoothly!!

originalText.text: Caroline was the single BEST choice we made for our entire wedding process. Her work is breathtaking - we've received so many compliments on our engagement and wedding photos as well as guests who vow to fly her out to their destination when it's their turn to have a wedding. She is sweet as can be and such a calming presence which is key on your wedding day when things are nuts and you're being pulled in a million directions. Finally - we heard from numerous guests that they have never been to a wedding where the photographer looked so visibly happy to be doing what she's doing. There really is no better choice than Caroline for your important events, we are so lucky we found her!

originalText.text: We were SO happy we hired Caroline as our wedding photographer and were very impressed with her work! We loved her photography style and also felt very comfortable with her when we met her before booking.  She was responsive and organized throughout the planning stages and she, her second shooter, and assistant were very pleasant during our wedding day.  Caroline and her team were assertive, efficient, and patient when needed to be (i.e. during family portraits) and not even noticeable during those special wedding day moments (first look, first dance, etc.).  We really ended up relying on her to direct the day, as we had some issues with the day-of coordinator at our venue.  We received our photos in a really reasonable time (and loved them!!!!) and appreciated that she started us off with a draft album for us to edit - it would be way to overwhelming to start from scratch!  Price-wise, her services cost more than we wanted to spend, but she is definitely a high-quality vendor.  If photography is important to you, as it was to us, she is well worth it!

originalText.text:
Dear Caroline Frost, photographer extraordinaire, and sweetest wedding vendor ever,

How can I ever thank you enough for the wonderful wedding photos you captured for Perry L and me? For your proactive assurance that every little detail would be fine, enthusiastic can-do attitude, infinite kind patience, and willingness to jump in and have fun? For your honesty, gentleness, and forthrightness in a crazy wedding industry? And most of all, for your artistic, down to earth, romantic vision that just set your photographs apart from the pack?

You were prepared at every single one of our meetings, with check lists, sample books, and a big smile. The engagement shoot was so much fun, even for introverts like Perry and me. And by the time the big day came, we were so comfortable in front of your camera. We hesitated about doing a first look but after you convinced us, it was absolutely the best part of the wedding day and some of my favorite shots. Your communication was impeccable and timely. You made the whole process joyful, full of small surprises, and reminded us why we were getting married in the first place. In addition, your personality made it so easy for you to blend in with the wedding guests and I really hope you had fun with us!

Even after the wedding, you continued to delight us in delivering photos quickly and throwing us a little viewing party. I loved the fantastic web gallery and album drafting tools you used - they were super easy and intuitive. Our album is phenomenal. The thank you cards were exactly what we wanted. And every single one of your shots is true to your style and vision. It was so EASY and FUN to work with you!

I apologize profusely for taking so long to write how much I admire the work you did and for not shouting it from the rooftops sooner. You are so talented, and I couldn't be happier with the memories we made that day.

Love and kisses,
Suanne L
